The Federal Government has created a unified platform for unemployed youths in the 36 states of the federation in line with the priority focus of President Muhammadu Buhari to create jobs for the teeming Nigerian youths and lift 100 million Nigerians out of poverty in the next 10 years. Minister of Youth and Sports Development, Mr. Sunday Dare, disclosed this while speaking after a three-day sensitisation workshop on the use of the Nigeria Online Youth Assembly (NOYA) platform held at the National Youth Development Centre in Ode-Omu, Osun State. Dare, represented at the event by Director of Procurement in the ministry, Mr. Segun Oke, said the platform was created for youths to have access to timely information on job opportunities.